description:
In what might be the easiest ride of the entire journey, we follow the river path in Philosopher's path in Kyoto all the way to Osaka Castle in Osaka.

Beginning on the Kamo River, we quickly join the Katsura River before crossing the Uji and Kizu Rivers in order to follow the Yodo River all the way to Osaka. The biggest obstacle of this ride is the countless gates dotted along the river path, so tight as to force us off our bikes every few hundred metres.
